c({"name": "can.Control.prototype.control", "params": {"control": {"description": "<p>(optional) if exists, the first control instance with this class type will be returned.</p>", "type": "Object", "optional": false, "order": 0, "name": "control"}}, "ret": {"description": "<p>the first control.</p>", "type": "can.Control"}, "type": "function", "comment": "<p>When the widget is initialized, the plugin control creates an array \nof the control instance with the DOM element it was initialized on using \n[can.data] method.</p>\n\n<p>The <code>control</code> method allows you to get the control instance for any element.  </p>\n\n<pre><code>    &lt;div class=\"widgets my_box\" /&gt;\n    $('.widgets').controls() //- will return: MyBox,\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Additionally, you can invoke it passing the name of a control\nto fetch a specific instance.</p>\n\n<pre><code>    &lt;div class=\"widgets my_box my_clock\" /&gt;\n    $('.widgets').control('MyBox') //- will return: MyBox\n</code></pre>", "parents": ["can.Control.plugin"], "src": "can/control/plugin/plugin.js", "line": 108, "children": []})